*[[1657]] &amp;ndash; [[Bohdan Khmelnytsky]], Ukrainian hetman (b. 1595)
*[[1660]] &amp;ndash; [[Diego Velázquez]], Spanish painter (b. 1599)
*[[1679]] &amp;ndash; [[John Snell]], Scottish-English founder of the [[Snell Exhibition]] (b. 1629)
*[[1694]] &amp;ndash; [[Antoine Arnauld]], French philosopher and mathematician (b. 1612)
*[[1695]] &amp;ndash; [[François de Harlay de Champvallon]], French archbishop (b. 1625)
*[[1753]] &amp;ndash; [[Georg Wilhelm Richmann]], Russian physicist (b. 1711)
*[[1757]] &amp;ndash; [[Ádám Mányoki]], Hungarian painter (b. 1673)
*[[1759]] &amp;ndash; [[Eugene Aram]], English philologist (b. 1704)
*[[1794]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry Bathurst, 2nd Earl Bathurst]], English lawyer and politician (b. 1714)
*[[1815]] &amp;ndash; [[James A. Bayard (elder)|James A. Bayard]], American politician (b. 1767)
*[[1828]] &amp;ndash; [[Konstantin von Benckendorff]], Russian general and diplomat (b. 1785)
*[[1850]] &amp;ndash; [[Edward Walsh (poet)|Edward Walsh]], Irish poet (b. 1805)
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; [[John Mason Neale]], English scholar and hymnwriter (b. 1818)
*[[1881]] &amp;ndash; [[James Springer White]], American preacher and author, co-founder of the [[Seventh-day Adventist Church]] (b. 1821)
*[[1884]] &amp;ndash; [[Robert Spear Hudson]], English businessman (b. 1812)
*[[1890]] &amp;ndash; [[William Kemmler]], American murderer (b. 1860)
*[[1893]] &amp;ndash; [[Jean-Jacques Challet-Venel]], Swiss politician (b. 1811)
*[[1904]] &amp;ndash; [[Eduard Hanslick]], Austrian critic (b. 1825)
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[Ellen Axson Wilson]], American wife of [[Woodrow Wilson]], 29th [[First Lady of the United States]] (b. 1860)
*[[1920]] &amp;ndash; [[Stefan Bastyr]], Polish pilot and author (b. 1890)
*[[1925]] &amp;ndash; [[Surendranath Banerjee]], Indian leader of the [[Indian National Congress]] (b. 1848)
*[[1931]] &amp;ndash; [[Bix Beiderbecke]], American cornetist, pianist, and composer ([[The Wolverines]]) (b. 1903)
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Bong]], American pilot, [[Medal of Honor]] recipient (b. 1920)
*  1945   &amp;ndash; [[Hiram Johnson]], American politician (b. 1866)
*  1945   &amp;ndash; [[Yi Wu]], Korean prince and army officer (b. 1912)
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; [[Tony Lazzeri]], American baseball player (b. 1903)
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; [[Ernest Linton]], Canadian football player (b. 1880)
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; [[Preston Sturges]], American playwright, screenwriter, and director (b. 1898)
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Cedric Hardwicke]], English actor (b. 1893)
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Cordwainer Smith]], American writer (b. 1913)
*[[1969]] &amp;ndash; [[Theodor W. Adorno]], German sociologist and philosopher (b. 1903)
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikos Tsiforos]], Greek screenwriter and director (b. 1912)
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; [[Fulgencio Batista]], Cuban military leader and politician, [[List of Presidents of Cuba|President of Cuba]] (b. 1901)
*  1973   &amp;ndash; [[Memphis Minnie]], American singer-songwriter (b. 1897)
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Gene Ammons]], American saxophonist (b. 1925)
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Gregor Piatigorsky]], Russian-American cellist (b. 1903)
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Paul VI]] (b. 1897)
*  1978   &amp;ndash; [[Edward Durell Stone]], American architect, designed [[Radio City Music Hall]] and the [[Kennedy Center]] (b. 1902)
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[Feodor Felix Konrad Lynen]], German biochemist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1911)
*[[1983]] &amp;ndash; [[Klaus Nomi]], German singer-songwriter and actor (b. 1944)
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Forbes Burnham]], Guyanese politician, 2nd [[President of Guyana]] (b. 1923)
*[[1986]] &amp;ndash; [[Emilio Fernández]], Mexican actor, screenwriter, and director (b. 1904)
*[[1987]] &amp;ndash; [[Ira C. Eaker]], American general (b. 1896)
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacques Soustelle]], French anthropologist (b. 1912)
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Shapour Bakhtiar]], Iranian politician, 74th [[Prime Minister of Iran]] (b. 1915)
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Roland Michener]], Canadian lawyer, politician, and diplomat, 20th [[Governor General of Canada]] (b. 1900)
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Harry Reasoner]], American journalist (b. 1923)
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Leszek Błażyński]], Polish boxer (b. 1949)
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[Tex Hughson]], American baseball player (b. 1916)
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; [[Domenico Modugno]], Italian singer-songwriter, actor, and politician (b. 1928)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[André Weil]], French mathematician (b. 1906)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Rita Sakellariou]], Greek singer (b. 1934)
